            "body": "Thanks guys, after these changes tailwindcss-lsp is working again (in rails views)\r\n\r\nBut only works for classes like: `class=\"flex flex\"` but not for `class: 'flex flex'`\r\n\r\nIf someone is having the same problem we can update the settings like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.lsp.config(\"tailwindcss\", {\r\n  settings = {\r\n    tailwindCSS = {\r\n      experimental = {\r\n        classRegex = {\r\n\t  \"class:? [\\\\\\\"\\\\']([^\\\\\\\"\\\\']*)[\\\\\\\"\\\\']\", -- Dynamic class strings\r\n\t},\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n})\r\n\r\n```",
